in_class_description_detail: Sand is any soft-bottom area dominated by fine unconsolidated sediments.
Rubble is any habitat featuring loose, rough fragments of broken reef material.
Rock is any exposed area of hard bare substrate.
Seagrass is any habitat where seagrass is the dominant biota.
Coral/Algae is any hard-bottom area supporting living coral and/or algae.
Microalgal Mats are any visible accumulations of microscopic algae in sandy sediments.
